results.title: Emulation of Decisive Battles of the American Civil War, Vol. 3 for Commodore 64
results.brief_description:
The third volume of the Decisive Battles of the American Civil War series allows the player to reenact another six crucial battles of the American Civil War: Wilderness, Spotsylvania, Cold Harbor, Atlanta, Franklin, Nashville. Just as the first and second volume, this turn-based, hex-based wargame focuses on simulating the limited control, communication and “fog of war” of a 19th-century battlefield, providing a challenge to the player taking command of either North or South forces. Apart from single and two player gameplay option, an editor is also available, enabling the creation of own scenarios.

Original game developed by Strategic Studies Group for Commodore 64, published in 1988 by Strategic Studies Group

results.title: Emulation of Russia The Great War in the East 1941-1945 or Commodore 64
results.brief_description:
Russia: The Great War in the East 1941-1945 is a turn & hex-based wargame. The player takes the role of either German Oberkommando des Heeres or Soviet Stavka, conducting the full Eastern Front campaign of the Second World War (4 years lasting 47 turns) - three smaller scenarios are also available (portions of the main campaign focusing exclusively on either Army Group North, Centre or South). The menu-driven interface is similar to earlier titles from the Battlefront Game System series, however it was modified for strategical level of command (army group/army), with corps-sized units moving under computer control, as you assign objectives (and stance) only to armies - particular corps may be later ordered to attack, defend, rest or retreat.

Original game developed by Strategic Studies Group Pty Ltd. Published in 1988 by Strategic Studies Group Pty Ltd.

results.brief_description: Judge Dredd [computer game]. Judge Dredd is a single player action platformer. Players move Dredd to locations of crime as they appear on the sector map and select the crime they wish to pass judgement on. Once a crime has been selected, Dredd is dropped into a side scrolling platformer where both perps and civilians roam. Each crime is given an appropriate response level of Halt, Warn and Kill, though it is up to player discretion to change the response level. Depending on the response level is the action Dredd can perform, either shouting halt, firing warning shots or firing real bullets. Dredd can select a type of bullet from normal, armour piercing, incendiary, ricochet, high explosive and heat seeking.

results.title: Emulation of Decisive Battles of the American Civil War, Vol. 2 for Commodore 64
results.brief_description:
The second volume of the Decisive Battles of the American Civil War series allows the player to reenact another five crucial battles of the American Civil War: Gaines Mill, Stones River, Gettysburg, Chickamauga, Chattanooga. Just as the first volume, this turn-based, hex-based wargame focuses on simulating the limited control, communication and “fog of war” of a 19th-century battlefield, providing a challenge to the player taking command of either North or South forces. Apart from single and two player gameplay option, an editor is also available, enabling the creation of own scenarios.

Original game developed by Strategic Studies Group for Commodore 64, published in 1988 by Strategic Studies Group

results.title: Emu
results.brief_description:
An intriguing and entertaining piece of work about an emu and her chick as they meander their way through urban streets in outback Broken Hill, NSW, confronting various challenges along the way. With no narration and using a music soundtrack this appealing doco captures the endearing qualities of these amazing Ozzie birds.
Camera, editing and music by Sean O’Keeffe.
